}} or search for something else.",home:"home",title:"The page you're looking for can't be found."}}},SomethingWentWrongPage:{authStatusAll:{message:{cta:"{{reloadLink}} or go {{homeLink}}.",home:"home",reloadThisPage:"Reload this page",title:"Something went wrong."}}},autoTagPage:{authStatusAll:{breadcrumb:{labelThree:"Topics",labelTwo:"Learn"},exploreContent:"Explore content",feed:{button:"Load more"},rightSide:{cta:"View all",section:"Trending topics"},trendingTopics:{cta:"View all",title:"Trending topics"}},authStatusPostAuth:{tabArticle:{tab:"Articles"},tabWish:{tab:"Wishes"}}},breadcrumbs:{editPost:"Edit Post",post:"Post"},buildPage:{authStatusAll:{breadcrumb:{labelTwo:"Build"},description:"Build with AWS. Practice, and prepare, and get hands-on experience to help you build with AWS.",hero:{subTitle:"Put your knowledge into practice.",title:"Build on AWS"},sectionActivateCredits:{body:"Are you a new startup building with AWS? Your startup can apply to receive up to $100,000 in AWS Activate Credits to use on 200+ eligible AWS services.",cta:"Apply for credits",label:"AWS Activate",title:"Promotional credits for startups"},sectionBuildQDev:{body:"Kiro helps builders with a range of tasks— from coding, testing, and deploying, to troubleshooting, performing security scanning and fixes, modernizing applications, optimizing AWS resources, and creating data engineering pipelines. {{linkComponent}}",bodyOne:"Use the Kiro agentic IDE to help you do your best work with features such as specs, steering, hooks, agentic chat, and MCP servers.",bodyThree:"Kiro autonomous agent works independently on development tasks, from features to bug fixes, in isolated sandboxes. It learns from your code reviews to understand your codebase and patterns.",bodyTwo:"Bring the power of AI-assisted development to your terminal with Kiro CLI. Build, test, and deploy applications using natural language commands and automated workflows.",ctaOne:"Get started",ctaThree:"Get started",ctaTwo:"Get started",labelOne:"",labelThree:"",labelTwo:"",learnMoreLink:"Learn more",title:"Start building with Kiro",titleOne:"Kiro IDE",titleThree:"Kiro autonomous agent",titleTwo:"Kiro CLI"},sectionExploreAI:{body:"Start exploring how to create scalable next-generation generative AI and agentic AI services.",bodyFive:"From inside the AWS Management Console, use Amazon Nova models to chat using text, images, or videos, generate images, or have voice conversations.",bodyFour:"With Amazon Nova Act, you can build computer agents that reliably take actions in web browsers, available as a research preview.",bodyOne:"From inside the AWS Management Console, create images, videos, and text in Amazon Bedrock playgrounds using straightforward prompts. Build on your results through contextual follow-up prompts in a conversational format.",bodySix:"From inside the AWS Management Console, create and configure an agent that can respond to user queries about the current date and time by invoking a Lambda function.",bodyThree:"Before going into the AWS Management Console, generate high-quality images using text and image inputs; chat using text, images, or videos; and have voice conversations using Amazon Nova models.",bodyTwo:"Use AWS PartyRock as a fast and fun way to learn about generative AI as you build AI generated apps in this Amazon Bedrock-powered playground. No console access needed.",ctaFive:"Get started",ctaFour:"Check out the preview",ctaOne:"Explore the playground",ctaSix:"Try the tutorial",ctaThree:"Try Amazon Nova",ctaTwo:"Try PartyRock",labelFive:"Generative AI",labelFour:"Agentic AI",labelOne:"Generative AI",labelSix:"Agentic AI",labelThree:"Generative AI",labelTwo:"Generative AI",title:"Explore AWS AI services",titleFive:"Amazon Nova in Amazon Bedrock",titleFour:"Build AI Agents with Amazon Nova",titleOne:"Amazon Bedrock playgrounds",titleSix:"Build Amazon Bedrock agent",titleThree:"Experiment with Amazon Nova",titleTwo:"AI-generated app building with AWS PartyRock"},sectionFreeTier:{body:"Have a new idea to test or just want to get hands-on with a new service in the console? Use the AWS Free Tier to explore and try out AWS services free of charge up to specified limits for each service.",cta:"Get started",title:"Leverage the Free Tier"},sectionHandsOn:{body:"Discover ways to get familiar with AWS through hands-on keyboard instruction by exploring interactive learning resources designed for every skill level.",bodyOne:"Find practical, step-by-step approaches to learning AWS. Tutorials are designed to help gain practical experience with various AWS services and solutions.",bodyThree:"AWS ramp-up guides offer a variety of resources to help you build your skills and knowledge of the AWS Cloud. Each guide features carefully selected digital training, classroom courses, videos, whitepapers, certifications, and more.",bodyTwo:"Find workshop events designed to teach or introduce practical skills, techniques, or concepts which you can use to solve business problems.",ctaOne:"Find a tutorial",ctaThree:"Download a ramp-up guide",ctaTwo:"Find a workshop",labelOne:"Inside the console",labelThree:"Inside the console",labelTwo:"Outside the console",title:"Get hands-on experience with AWS",titleOne:"AWS Tutorials",titleThree:"AWS Ramp-Up Guides",titleTwo:"AWS Workshops"}}},cardActionReport:{archive:"Archive",cancel:"Cancel",cardActionReport:{archive:"Archive",cancel:"Cancel",closeModalAriaLabel:"Close modal",delete:"Delete",edit:"Edit",linkToComment:"Link to comment:",optionalLabel:"- optional",reasonLabel:"Reason for suspending",reasonPlaceholder:"Describe the reason for suspending",reportError:"An error occurred when trying to report this content.",reportQuestion:"What type of issue are you reporting?",reportSuccessMessage:"This content has been reported successfully. A moderator will review and take appropriate action.",selectReasonError:"Please select a reason for reporting this content.",shareAdditionalPlaceholder:"Any additional information?",shareAdditionalReport:"Do you have any additional information that will help us understand and handle the situation?",signInToReport:"Sign in to report content.",signInToSuspend:"Sign in to suspend this content.",suspendActionHeadline:"You are about to suspend this content",unsuspendAction:"Unsuspend",unsuspendActionHeadline:"You are about to unsuspend this content"},closeModalAriaLabel:"Close modal",delete:"Delete",edit:"Edit",linkToComment:"Link to comment:",optionalLabel:"- optional",reasonLabel:"Reason for suspending",reasonPlaceholder:"Describe the reason for suspending",reportError:"An error occurred when trying to report this content.",reportQuestion:"What type of issue are you reporting?",reportSuccessMessage:"This content has been reported successfully. A moderator will review and take appropriate action.",selectReasonError:"Please select a reason for reporting this content.",shareAdditionalPlaceholder:"Any additional information?",shareAdditionalReport:"Do you have any additional information that will help us understand and handle the situation?",signInToReport:"Sign in to report content.",signInToSuspend:"Sign in to suspend this content.",suspendActionHeadline:"You are about to suspend this content",unsuspendAction:"Unsuspend",unsuspendActionHeadline:"You are about to unsuspend this content"},commentSection:{buttonLoadMore:"Load more",buttonSignIn:"Sign in",emptyCommentsDescription:"Be the first to comment!",endOfMessageTitle:"No more comments to display",errorMessage:"Unable to add comment. Please try later",joinButton:"Join",joinToCommentTemplate:"Join {{spaceLink}} to comment.",signInToCommentLabel:"Sign in to comment"},commentUser:{buttonLoadMore:"Load more",deleteModalDescription:"This comment will be deleted and cannot be recovered.",deleteModalHeader:"Delete comment?",loadingLabel:"Loading...",modifiedPrefix:"Modified",seeMoreComments:"See more Comments",signInModalCommentDesc:({appNameShort:e})=>`Join ${e} to respond to this content.`,signInModalCommentHeader:"Leave a comment"},connectPage:{authStatusAll:{breadcrumb:{labelOne:"AWS Builder Center",labelTwo:"Connect"},description:"Connect with the AWS builder community, attend events, meet cloud builders, grow your skills.",hero:{subTitle:"Find community, meet cloud builders, grow your skills.",title:"Connect"},sectionCommunityDays:{body:"AWS Community Days are conferences organized and led by local AWS experts. These events feature technical talks, workshops, and labs that enable peer-to-peer learning among builders.",cta:"Find upcoming events",label:"Builder-created events",title:"AWS Community Days"},sectionEventsBuilders:{body:"Join upcoming AWS events, workshops, and webinars to enhance your cloud skills and network with experts.",bodyOne:"Meet and learn with other builders at industry-expert sessions, hands-on workshops, and community-driven events in the heart of San Franscico.",bodyThree:"Free technical workshops and networking sessions designed to help startup founders and developers build and scale their products efficiently on AWS.",bodyTwo:"Technical sessions and workshops for builders to learn about AWS services and best practices from AWS Partners and experts.",ctaOne:"Find upcoming events",ctaThree:"Find upcoming events",ctaTwo:"Find upcoming events",linkText:"Explore more events",title:"Events for AWS Builders",titleOne:"AWS Builder Loft events",titleThree:"AWS Startups events",titleTwo:"AWS Partner events"},sectionExploreCommunity:{bodyFive:"Connecting with a builder community gives you the support to grow your career and skills in the cloud. Explore all AWS communities.",bodyFour:"Student Builder Groups are vibrant, student-led communities on post-secondary school campuses. Find your local group to meet your peers, explore cloud technology, build innovative projects, and grow your technical skills.",bodyOne:"Meet the technical experts building innovative solutions on AWS. Their enthusiasm for sharing their knowledge and expertise with AWS Builders around the world continues to make a valuable impact within the community.",bodyThree:"Discover your local community-led AWS User Group, where builders meet to discuss the latest in AWS Cloud, learn new skills from like-minded peers, and network with builders in their local AWS community.",bodyTwo:"Get familiar with AWS Cloud enthusiasts and emerging thought leaders who are passionate about sharing knowledge and connecting with the technical community.",ctaFive:"Find communities",ctaFour:"Find your group",ctaOne:"Meet the Heroes",ctaThree:"Find your group",ctaTwo:"Meet the Community Builders",labelFive:"More communities for AWS Builders",labelFour:"Student meetups",labelOne:"Recognized experts",labelThree:"Community meetups",labelTwo:"Enthusiasts and emerging leaders",title:"Explore communities",titleFive:"Discover more communities",titleFour:"AWS Student Builder Groups",titleOne:"AWS Heroes",titleThree:"AWS User Groups",titleTwo:"AWS Community Builders"},sectionSocials:{title:"Join the conversation"}}},createArticlePage:{authStatusPostAuth:{action:{buttonPreview:"Preview",buttonPublish:"Publish"},body:{markdownCheatsheet:"Markdown cheatsheet",placeholder:"What do you want to share?",section:"Body"},breadcrumb:{labelTwo:"Create an article"},canonicalUrl:{description:"If you've published this content elsewhere, this is the URL of the main version. This helps avoid duplicate content issues, improving SEO.",section:"Canonical URL"},description:{description:"One or two sentences summarizing your article without repeating the title. This appears in search results and feeds.",placeholder:"Description",section:"Description"},imageUpload:{button:"Upload image",description:"The recommended size is 1200px × 675px. The maximum file size is 2 MB. Text in images is not recommended.",section:"Upload a cover image - optional"},legalStatement:{awsBuilderTerms:"AWS Builder Terms",description:"Please read and understand the {{awsBuilderTerms}} before creating content."},limitPopup:{closeAriaLabel:"Close quota modal",createLimitDescription:"Thanks for being an active contributor! You can create a new article in an hour.",createLimitTitle:"You've reached the create limit for articles",publishLimitDescription:"Thanks for being an active contributor! Your next article can be published at:",publishLimitTitle:"You've reached the daily publish limit for articles",reviewLimitDescription:"Thanks for being an active contributor! Your next article can be reviewed in an hour.",reviewLimitTitle:"You've reached the hourly review limit for articles"},main:{header:"Create an article",yourDrafts:"Your drafts",yourDraftsSaved:"Saved to {{yourDrafts}}"},series:{addNewButton:"Add new series",clearButton:"Remove from series",createError:"Failed to create series. Please try again.",createSuccess:"Series created successfully.",description:"Add this article to a series to organize your content for readers.",emptyText:'No series yet. Use "Add new series" to create one.',errorText:"Failed to load series",loadingText:"Loading series",modalCancel:"Cancel",modalHeader:"Create series",placeholder:"Choose a series",section:"Series"},tags:{countTags:"5 maximum",description:"Relevant tags help readers discover and search for your article.",placeholder:"Choose tags",section:"Tags"},title:{description:"This appears in search results and in feeds. It should be short, descriptive, and unique.",placeholder:"Title",section:"Title"}}},editArticlePage:{authStatusPostAuth:{breadcrumb:{labelTwo:"Edit article"},main:{header:"Edit article"}}},editSeriesPage:{authStatusPostAuth:{actions:{buttonCancel:"Cancel",buttonSave:"Save"},articles:{addButton:"Add article",ariaLabel:"Articles in the series",empty:"No articles in this series.",label:"Articles in the series",newArticle:"New article",removeAriaLabel:({title:e})=>`Remove ${e} from series`},breadcrumb:{ariaLabel:"Edit series breadcrumb",labelContent:"Content",labelTwo:"Edit series"},deleteSeries:{cancel:"Cancel",closeAriaLabel:"Close delete series modal",confirm:"Remove article",description:"A series must have at least one article. Removing this article will delete the series, but keep the article intact. You can't undo this action.",error:"Failed to delete series. Please try again.",header:"Removing this article deletes the series",success:"Series deleted successfully."},errors:{duplicateTitle:"This series title is already in use.",loadErrorBody:"The series could not be loaded. Go back and try again.",loadErrorHeader:"Failed to load series",saveErrorFlashbar:"Failed to update series",saveErrorInline:"Failed to update series. Please try again."},main:{header:"Edit series",metaDescription:"Edit an article series"},select:{alreadyInSeries:"This article is already in a series",draftDescription:"Draft (only visible to you until you publish the article)",loadArticlesError:"Failed to load articles",loadingText:"Loading articles",placeholder:"Choose an article",untitled:"Untitled"},success:{saveSuccess:"Series updated successfully."},title:{characterCount:({current:e,max:t})=>`Character count: ${e}/${t}`,description:"This appears on articles within the series. It should be short, descriptive, and unique.",label:"Series title",placeholder:"Series title"}}},errorMessages:{invalidImageURLError:'Invalid image URL. Upload your image using the "Insert image" button in the toolbar.',moderationCheckFailed:"Moderation check failed. Please review your input and try again.",shortenedURLError:"Shortened URLs are not allowed. Remove to publish.",unknownError:"Unknown error",unsupportedDomainError:'Invalid image URL. Upload your image using the "Insert image" button in the toolbar.',uploadFailedUnknownError:"Upload failed due to an unknown error."},formValidation:{articleSchema:{bodyMaxLength:({maxLength:e})=>`Article must be under ${e} characters`,bodyRequired:"Body is required",descriptionMaxLength:({maxLength:e})=>`Description must be under ${e} characters`,descriptionRequired:"Description is required",imageMaxSize:"Image must be less than 2 MB.",tagsInvalid:({invalidTags:e})=>`Your selection has tags that are not supported on Builder Center: ${e}. Remove tags that aren't valid.`,tagsMaxCount:({maxCount:e})=>`You can select up to ${e} tags`,titleMaxLength:({maxLength:e})=>`Title must be under ${e} characters`,titleRequired:"Title is required"},descriptionFormField:"Description",emailFormField:"Email",emailInvalid:"Enter a valid email address",featureFormField:"Feature",httpsUrl:({httpsPrefix:e})=>`Enter a valid URL starting with "${e}".`,justificationFormField:"Justification",mandatoryFieldMessage:({field:e})=>`${e} is required`,moreOptions:"More options",nameFormField:"Name",optionalFormFieldLabel:({formFieldLabel:e})=>`${e} {{optionalFormFieldLabelSuffix}}`,optionalFormFieldLabelSuffix:"- optional",reasonFormField:"Reason",requestDescriptionFormField:"Request description",selectionFormField:"Selection",seriesSchema:{titleMaxLength:({maxLength:e})=>`Series title must be under ${e} characters`,titleRequired:"Series title is required"},urlFormField:"URL"},heroesPage:{authStatusAll:{asideFAQ:{answerEight:"While we're always on the lookout for the next group of AWS Heroes, note this isn't a definitive checklist or direct path to become one. If you'd like to be considered for recognition in the AWS Heroes program, make sure you're contributing and sharing AWS knowledge with the community.\n\nCheckout the _AWS News Blog_ to stay up to date on the latest news and updates on the AWS Heroes program.",answerFive:"AWS Heroes are community leaders who drive innovation within the AWS community through technical content, public speaking, community events, and open-source contributions. Both Community and Specialized Heroes play crucial roles in growing and strengthening the global AWS community, each contributing their unique perspective and expertise to help cloud practitioners, developers, and organizations succeed in their AWS journey. Here's how Community and Specialized Heroes differ in their areas of expertise:",answerFour:"The AWS Hero nomination and selection process consists of three main phases:\n\n• *Nomination Process:* AWS Heroes are nominated by Amazon employees who recognize exceptional community contributions made independently of the nominee's employer.\n\n• *Evaluation*: A dedicated committee conducts quarterly reviews to assess candidates' authentic community engagement and impact.\n\n• *Selection:* Final selections prioritize technical excellence, meaningful contributions, and sustained community involvement. The committee values consistent, independent community leadership over individual achievements like certifications.",answerNine:"Community Heroes are passionate enthusiasts who educate builders on AWS, build and nurture local communities, and share knowledge through various mediums like blogs, talks, and meetups; while they may have specific areas of expertise, their primary focus is advocating for the full spectrum of AWS services.",answerOne:"The purpose of the AWS Heroes program is to recognize and honor the most engaged and influential builders who have a significant impact within the AWS community. It also provides Heroes a place to tell their story and connect with like-minded builders. If you are looking to learn from and connect with experienced members of the AWS community, check out their bios and connect online.",answerSeven:"_AWS Ambassadors_ are certified professionals from AWS Partner Network (APN) organizations who:\n\n• Drive AWS expertise internally at their organization\n• Create public technical content\n• Support regional communities through events and publications\n\nAWS Ambassadors can become AWS Heroes, but Heroes can only be Ambassadors if employed by qualified AWS Partners. Hero-Ambassadors contribute beyond their APN firms to support global and local AWS communities without renumeration.\n",answerSix:"The _AWS Community Builders_ program is an application-based community of thousands of worldwide builders. The program helps builders up-skill and share their journey by providing learning and growth opportunities, and access to a vast network of other builders.\n\nBeing an AWS Community Builder isn't a requirement for becoming a Hero. The program does provide builders unique opportunities to deepen their support and contributions to the AWS community.",answerTen:"Specialized Heroes, also known as Category Heroes, are early adopters and thought leaders within specific AWS technology domains. They focus exclusively on specific AWS technologies, while bringing deep expertise to their chosen domain and guiding builders through advanced AWS solutions implementations. Specialized Hero categories include:\n\n**• Container Heroes**: Guide DevOps teams and container enthusiasts in leveraging Amazon container services\n**•* ***Data Heroes**: Support data scientists and analysts in using AWS analytics, database, and blockchain technologies\n**•* ***DevTools Heroes**: Enhance the developer experience on AWS, helping software engineers optimize their workflows\n**•* ***Machine Learning Heroes**: Assist data scientists and ML engineers in implementing AWS-based ML solutions\n**•* ***Security Heroes**: Advise cybersecurity professionals and IT teams on best practices for secure AWS implementations\n**•* ***Serverless Heroes**: Aid developers and architects in adopting serverless architectures on AWS",answerThree:"We aim to encourage and recognize genuine, authentic, and meaningful contributions, which creates and fosters a community interested in continuing to invest heavily in others. Thus, there is no checklist of precise actions one can take to become a Hero.\n\nSome key characteristics of an AWS Hero include:\n\n• *Enthusiasm:* An individual who regularly participates, engages, and motivates the AWS community\n\n• *Expertise:* Being an expert in AWS and staying on top of trends\n\n• *Leadership:* Building relationships and strengthening ties within the community\n\n• *Selflessness:* Delivering impact to communities without thought of remuneration or self-benefit",answerTwo:"AWS Heroes are mentors and expert users who provide valuable content to the global AWS community through:\n\n• Writing blog posts, articles, books, and technical documentation\n• Creating tutorials, podcasts, and videos\n• Contributing to open source projects and sharing code samples\n• Organizing AWS-focused events such as AWS User Groups, hackathons, workshops, and AWS Community Days\n• Speaking at tech events worldwide\n",questionEight:"How do I find more information about the AWS Heroes program?",questionFive:"What is the difference between a Community Hero and a Specialized Hero?",questionFour:"What is the process for becoming a Hero?",questionNine:"**What is a Community Hero?**",questionOne:"What is the AWS Heroes program?",questionSeven:"How is the AWS Ambassador Partner program different from the AWS Heroes program?",questionSix:"How is the AWS Community Builders program different from the AWS Heroes program?",questionTen:"**What is a Specialized Hero?**",questionThree:"What does AWS look for in an AWS Hero?",questionTwo:"What does someone do when they become an AWS Hero?",sectionTitle:"FAQs"},breadcrumb:{labelTwo:"Community"},description:"AWS Heroes are technical experts building innovative solutions on AWS. They make a valuable impact in the community through their enthusiasm for sharing their knowledge and expertise with builders globally.",directory:{followAltTextHover:"Follow builder",followCTA:"Follow"},filter:{searchPlaceholder:"Find an AWS Hero",sectionCategory:"Category",sectionCategoryAIHero:"AI Hero",sectionCategoryAll:"All categories",sectionCategoryCommunityHero:"Community Hero",sectionCategoryContainerHero:"Container Hero",sectionCategoryDataHero:"Data Hero",sectionCategoryDevToolsHero:"DevTools Hero",sectionCategorySecurityHero:"Security Hero",sectionCategoryServerlessHero:"Serverless Hero",sectionCountry:"All countries"},hero:{body:"Recognized leaders in the community"},heroDetail:{about:"About",viewAllHeroes:"View all AWS Heroes",viewBuilderCenterActivity:"View Builder Center activity"},heroTypes:{sectionCategoryAIHero:"AI Hero",sectionCategoryCommunityHero:"Community Hero",sectionCategoryContainerHero:"Container Hero",sectionCategoryDataHero:"Data Hero",sectionCategoryDevToolsHero:"DevTools Hero",sectionCategorySecurityHero:"Security Hero",sectionCategoryServerlessHero:"Serverless Hero"},pageSection:{bodyAboutTheProgram:"The AWS Heroes program recognizes a vibrant, worldwide group of AWS experts whose enthusiasm for knowledge-sharing has a real impact within the community. Community and specialization focused Heroes go above and beyond to share knowledge in a variety of ways including online via social media, blog posts, open source projects, videos, and forums; or in person at conferences, workshops, and user group events.",learnMore:"Learn more"}},authStatusPostAuth:{directory:{following:"Following",threeDotsButtonAltTextHover:"Show more"}},title:"AWS Heroes"},homePage:{authStatusAll:{articleCard:{commentAltTextHover:"Comment on article",copyAltTextHover:"Copy article",copyButton:"Link copied",followAltTextHover:"Follow builder",followCTA:"Follow",likeAltTextHover:"Like article",threeDotsButtonAltTextHover:"Show more"},asideFollow:{followAltTextHover:"Follow builder",followCTA:"Follow",headline:"Who to follow"},asideSpace:{builderSpaces:"Spaces",exploreMore:"Explore more spaces",join:"Join",joinRequestResult:{fail:({spaceName:e})=>`An error occurred while joining ${e}. Try again.`,success:({spaceName:e})=>`You are now a member of ${e}.`},joinSpaceModal:{bodyText:"Sign in to Builder Center to join a space.",headerText:"Join space",signIn:"Sign in"},joined:"Joined",public:"Public",viewAll:"View all"},asideTrending:{sectionTrendingTopic:"Trending topics",viewAllCTA:"View all"},asideWishlist:{commentAltTextHover:"Comment on wish",copyAltTextHover:"Copy wish",copyButton:"Link copied",feedArticle:{t